subsection.p:
Atmospheric pressure equivalents: 


 \text{Atmospheric Pressure \amp= 14.7 \text{ psi} 
 \amp = 29.92 \textrm{ in Hg} 
 \amp = 760 \textrm{ mm Hg} 
 \amp = 34 \textrm{ ft H}_2\textrm{O} 
 \amp= 101.3 \textrm{ kPa} 
 \amp= 1.01 \textrm{ bar}


Absolute scales measure up from zero 

Gage scales measure up or down from atmospheric pressure 

Vacuum scales measure down from atmospheric pressure

li.p:
 Set up a ratio to convert psia to mm Hg Absolute 

\frac{10.4 \textrm{ psia}}{14.7 \textrm{ psia}} \amp= \frac{p}{760 \textrm{ mm Hg} }
\amp = 537.7 \textrm{ mm Hg (absolute)}
